 And maybe you could say a little bit about that.

00:04:35.080 --> 00:04:45.480
 When I ran into the biological dogmatism of the nerve people, they were basing everything

00:04:45.480 --> 00:04:53.040
 on an all or nothing function of nerve membrane.

00:04:53.040 --> 00:05:00.280
 From the reading I had been doing and some experiments, I was very skeptical about the

00:05:00.280 --> 00:05:06.200
 whole membrane control of cell biology.

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:15.800
 And starting from when I was about eight years old and read about the history of inheritance

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:23.920
 in the encyclopedias, I saw that there was very good evidence for the Lamarckian type

00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:31.240
 of inheritance all the way through the early decades of the 20th century.

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:40.080
 And it was essentially stamped out by not permitting any more teachers to describe the

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:45.640
 Lamarckian theory starting in 1947.

00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:56.560
 And that seeing that the modern biology people were explaining everything in terms of genes

00:05:56.560 --> 00:06:06.760
 and membranes, I looked around in the literature contemporary with what we were being assigned

00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:17.040
 and saw that Otto Warburg had solved most of the problems of how cancer develops, for

00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:28.040
 example, on the basis of damage to the respiratory energy producing system.

00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:39.120
 That was very convincing to me that people were ignoring him or denying his work had

00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:42.240
 any validity without even understanding it.

00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:47.520
 They always misquoted and misrepresented it.

00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:56.720
 At the same time, I ran into the work of Gilbert Ling in the early 1950s and saw that he had

00:06:56.720 --> 00:07:11.320
 demonstrated the irrelevancy of the so-called nerve membrane or cell membrane in general.

00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:21.440
 His work had basically solved all of the problems that my professors were working on and mystifying,

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:28.480
 really confusing and creating problems where there weren't any problems.

00:07:28.480 --> 00:07:38.280
 And I wrote to him, I think it was in the fall of '68, and said, "You seem to have solved

00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:42.160
 all of these problems that are confusing my professors."

00:07:42.160 --> 00:07:47.840
 And he said, "You just don't understand science.

00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:52.480
 Science is about prestige and money and power."

00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:59.880
 And I've written to him three times over the decades and he's been very helpful each time.

00:07:59.880 --> 00:08:05.560
 Yeah, he's a, I mean, I have his book and it's way over my head in terms of math and

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:16.200
 probably other things as well, but he is a brilliant man and just the face of it, his

