 And thank you for that.

00:09:05.640 --> 00:09:12.460
 But I think a lot of your research, Ray, has been about basically environmental influences

00:09:12.460 --> 00:09:20.920
 on life and countering basically the mainstream science who is saying it's all genetic, that

00:09:20.920 --> 00:09:26.680
 environment has very little influence on why we get sick or anything like that.

00:09:26.680 --> 00:09:28.320
 Would you say that's true?

00:09:28.320 --> 00:09:39.400
 Yeah, except that I see the mainstream as having been exactly where I've been, except

00:09:39.400 --> 00:09:45.040
 they got shut down financially and in publication.

00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:52.520
 The same time Lamarckism was extirpated from high schools and universities, the field theory

00:09:52.520 --> 00:10:04.520
 of embryology was definanced, just disappeared, even though it was the mainstream based on

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:06.800
 soundless facts.

00:10:06.800 --> 00:10:18.000
 The genetic control people, if you look at summaries of the classic papers in genetics,

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:24.720
 you see how hypothetical and rationalistic it is.

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:30.720
 It's sort of like it could happen approach to science.

00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:40.160
 And they define themselves as the mainstream simply by shutting off publication to the

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:42.780
 dissidents.

00:10:42.780 --> 00:10:53.120
 But now it's coming back, people like Shapiro with his bacterial demonstration of environmental

00:10:53.120 --> 00:10:59.600
 and transgenerational influences.

00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:09.800
 John Cairns is another bacteria person who has kept alive the influence of the environment

00:11:09.800 --> 00:11:15.240
 on inheritance.

00:11:15.240 --> 00:11:24.680
 There's been a continuous environmental, developmental field approach in all aspects of biology,

00:11:24.680 --> 00:11:30.280
 but they've been systematically quieted.

00:11:30.280 --> 00:11:32.520
 And it seems like there's some ideological reasons.

00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:38.600
 We've talked about these before, but there's also some very pointed financial reasons in

00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:45.600
 that if the environment does affect our health, it means that corporations that are polluting

00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:51.040
 that environment are basically doing it at our expense in dollars and also our expense

00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:56.680
 in quality of life because they're killing us by poisoning.

00:11:56.680 --> 00:12:00.000
 You can see that over and over.

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:05.400
 Every generation has its area of concentration.

00:12:05.400 --> 00:12:15.440
 The behaviorist psychologists basically defended poverty and oppression because they said what

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:23.880
 happens to the brain of the fetus in utero is purely genetically determined, so the mother

00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:25.800
 can be starved half to death.

00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:29.200
 That isn't going to hurt the offspring.

00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:39.440
 And the medical establishment went along with that, justifying basically starvation, living

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:42.040
 for the poor classes.

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:51.280
 Yeah, I mean, all the science influences public policy in an enormous way, and so it has had

00:12:51.280 --> 00:12:55.680
 huge repercussions.

00:12:55.680 --> 00:13:03.680
 The only time I had an actual employment contract was from the Catholic University of Chile.

00:13:03.680 --> 00:13:14.240
 And under the government in the early 70s, they were encouraged to do research on the

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:23.440
 influence of economic factors on the development of intelligence, and I got a job directing

00:13:23.440 --> 00:13:33.000
 a project in the influence of nutrition on brain development at the Catholic University

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:44.680
 in Valparaiso, and that was part of the social change that was shut down in the coup of 1973.

00:13:44.680 --> 00:13:53.880
 And the whole economic intellectual environment had progressed to that point that they were

00:13:53.880 --> 00:14:03.680
 interested in the fetal influences of nutrition, but the American influence wiped that out

00:14:03.680 --> 00:14:07.420
 with Kissinger and, you know, Tate.

