 We got speakers from 10 different departments, and each of them said, "Our departmental most

00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:31.840
 important insight to human nature is Chomsky's generative language theory, speaking of totalitarian

00:16:31.840 --> 00:16:32.840
 cultures."

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:41.800
 Yeah, so we're on the subject of humanities, and maybe we should get to Blake before the

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:45.960
 time whizzes by and we haven't had time to discuss it.

